By Nicholas Kalu, Abuja  The Inspector General of Police, Mohammed Adamu, has approved five new divisions in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Command of the Nigeria Police. They are Pegi Division, Biaji Division, Dawaki Division, Yebu Division and Galadima Division. A statement by FCT Police Public Relations Officer, ASP Mariam Yusuf, on behalf of the Commissioner of Police explained: “The creation of these divisions is in line with the Inspector-General of Police Adamu Mohammed Abubakar, NPM, mni concept of community policing which is intended to bring the Police closer to the community and jointly combat criminality in all ramifications. “Furthermore, the creation of these divisions was necessitated by population explosion, vast terrain and infrastructural availability in these areas. “The Command enjoins the public to cooperate with the operatives of these new divisions for effective and efficient policing. “The Command wishes to reassure the public of its unwavering commitment to tackle crime and ensure safety in the FCT. In case of emergency contact the Command through any of these emergency numbers: 08032003913, 08061581938, 07057337653 and 08028940883.”